.TH CLAUDII 1 "March 2026" "claudii 0.1.0" "claudii manual"
.
.SH NAME
claudii \- Claude Interaction Intelligence
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B claudii
.IR command " [" args ]
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B claudii
is a zsh plugin and CLI for Claude Code power users.
It monitors model health in the RPROMPT, shows context/cost/tokens inside
Claude Code sessions, handles auto-fallback to healthy models, and provides
debug logging and zsh autocomplete.
.
.SH COMMANDS
.
.SS ClaudeStatus
Monitors Claude API health in the shell RPROMPT.
Uses the Statuspage components API; falls back to the RSS feed for per-model incident details.
.
.TP
.B status
Show current model health (always live — bypasses the cache).
.
.TP
.BR status " on|off"
Enable or disable ClaudeStatus in the RPROMPT.
.
.TP
.BR status " 5m|15m|30m|60m"
Set the background cache refresh interval (default: 15m).
Values below 30s are rejected.
.
.TP
.B "show model"
Show the current list of models displayed in the RPROMPT.
.
.TP
.BI "show model " "opus sonnet haiku"
Replace the displayed model list (space-separated).
.
.TP
.BI "show model add " model
Add a model to the RPROMPT list.
.
.TP
.BI "show model rm " model
Remove a model from the RPROMPT list.
.
.SS Shell Aliases
Shell functions loaded by the zsh plugin for launching Claude Code.
Configured via
.B aliases.*
in config.
Auto-fallback to a healthy model when the configured model is down (see
.BR fallback.enabled ).
.
.TP
.B cl
Claude Sonnet, high effort. General-purpose default.
.TP
.B clo
Claude Opus, high effort. Complex tasks, server work.
.TP
.B clm
Claude Opus, max effort. Maximum reasoning.
.TP
.B clq
Claude Sonnet, medium effort. Search mode \(em launches in
.IR search.dir .
Equivalent to
.BR "claudii search" .
.TP
.B clh
Show the alias table and run a live model health check.
.
.SS Claude Code Status Line (by wynandw87)
Rendered inside Claude Code sessions via
.IR ~/.claude/settings.json .
Shows model name, context usage, cost, token counts, and rate limits.
Based on
.UR https://github.com/wynandw87/claude-code-statusline
wynandw87/claude-code-statusline
.UE .
.
.TP
.B sessionline
Show whether the Claude Code Status Line is active.
.
.TP
.B "sessionline on"
Add the Claude Code Status Line to
.IR ~/.claude/settings.json .
Restart Claude Code to activate.
.
.TP
.B "sessionline off"
Remove the Claude Code Status Line from
.IR ~/.claude/settings.json .
.
.SS Config
.
.TP
.B config
Show all config values (user config + path).
.
.TP
.BI "config get " key
Read a config value using dot-notation.
Example:
.BR "claudii config get aliases.cl.model" .
.
.TP
.BI "config set " "key value"
Set a config value.
Example:
.BR "claudii config set statusline.models opus,sonnet" .
.
.TP
.B "config reset"
Reset all config to defaults.
.
.TP
.BI "config export " "[file]"
Print config as JSON, or write to
.I file
if specified.
.
.TP
.BI "config import " file
Replace current config with a JSON file (backs up the existing config first).
.
.SS Debug Logging
.
.TP
.B debug
Show the current debug level.
.
.TP
.BR "debug " "off|error|warn|info|debug"
Set the log level.
.B off
(default) suppresses all output.
.B debug
is the most verbose.
The level can also be set via the environment variable
.BR CLAUDII_LOG_LEVEL .
.
.SS Other
.
.TP
.B metrics
Show performance metrics for this shell session: plugin load time, config load time
(jq), precmd hook timing (last / average / total), and config reload count.
.B Note:
This is a zsh shell function \(em it reads in-memory counters, not subprocess output.
.
.TP
.BI "search " "['query']"
Launch Claude Code in the configured search directory
.RI ( search.dir " in config, default:" " ~/claude-search" ).
Uses the
.B clq
alias settings (model + effort).
If
.I query
is provided, it is passed as the initial prompt to Claude Code.
.
.TP
.B restart
Reload the claudii plugin by sourcing
.I ~/.zshrc
in the current shell.
Stays in the current directory.
.B Note:
This is a zsh shell function, not a subprocess \(em it reloads the parent shell.
.
.TP
.B about
Show version, features, and the project URL.
.
.TP
.B version
Print the version string.
.
.SH CONFIG FILE
User config:
.I ~/.config/claudii/config.json
(or
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/claudii/config.json
if set).
Created automatically from defaults on first run.
.PP
Key paths (dot-notation):
.PP
.RS
.nf
aliases.cl.model        model for \fBcl\fR alias (default: sonnet)
aliases.cl.effort       effort for \fBcl\fR (default: high)
aliases.clo.model       model for \fBclo\fR (default: opus)
aliases.clm.effort      effort for \fBclm\fR (default: max)
aliases.clq.model       model for \fBclq\fR / search (default: sonnet)
fallback.enabled        auto-fallback on outage (default: true)
fallback.opus.model     fallback model when opus is down
status.cache_ttl        status cache TTL in seconds (default: 900)
status.rss_url          Claude status RSS feed URL
statusline.enabled      show ClaudeStatus in RPROMPT (default: true)
statusline.models       comma-separated model list (default: opus,sonnet,haiku)
debug.level             log level: off|error|warn|info|debug (default: off)
search.dir              directory for search mode (default: ~/claude-search)
.fi
.RE
.
.SH STATUS CACHE
The model status cache is stored at
.IR "${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-~/.cache}/claudii/status-models"
(overrideable via
.BR CLAUDII_CACHE_DIR ).
It persists across terminal sessions and reboots.
It contains one line per model:
.PP
.RS
.nf
opus=ok
sonnet=down
haiku=ok
.fi
.RE
.PP
The cache is refreshed automatically in the background when it exceeds
.B status.cache_ttl
seconds.
.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CLAUDII_HOME
Path to the claudii plugin directory. Set automatically by the plugin.
.TP
.B CLAUDII_CACHE_DIR
Override the cache directory (default:
.IR ${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-~/.cache}/claudii ).
Useful for testing or relocating the cache.
.TP
.B CLAUDII_LOG_LEVEL
Override the debug log level without writing to config.
Values: off, error, warn, info, debug.
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Overrides the config directory (default:
.IR ~/.config ).
.TP
.B XDG_CACHE_HOME
Overrides the base cache directory (default:
.IR ~/.cache ).
claudii uses
.IR $XDG_CACHE_HOME/claudii/ .
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/claudii/config.json
User configuration.
.TP
.I $CLAUDII_HOME/config/defaults.json
Shipped defaults (read-only reference).
.TP
.I ${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-~/.cache}/claudii/status-models
Per-model status cache, written by
.BR claudii-status (1).
Override with
.BR CLAUDII_CACHE_DIR .
.TP
.I ~/.claude/settings.json
Claude Code settings file, modified by
.BR "claudii sessionline" .
.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Activate the Claude Code Status Line:
.B claudii sessionline on
.TP
Show only Opus and Sonnet in RPROMPT:
.B claudii show model opus sonnet
.TP
Check every 5 minutes:
.B claudii status 5m
.TP
Enable verbose debug output:
.B claudii debug info
.TP
Read a config value:
.B claudii config get aliases.cl.model
.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR claude (1),
.BR jq (1),
.BR zsh (1)
.
